race.comment: Modest maiden for the older gallopers. MIDLIFE CRISIS (5) ran well at his only start before a break so there is definitely some talent there. He has had a couple of jumpouts in preparation for this so he should be ready to fire first-up. Draws well and gets a top jockey in Jacob Opperman. In a thin race, he's a winning chance. I AM RALPH (3) is an improving type that might be ready to peak. He maps to get all the favours. FAST TEMPO (1) has shown glimpses of ability in his career to date and, while he might be better over further than 1200m, he can run a cheeky race fresh. Others to consider are STRONG MINDED (7) and SHALHAVMUSIK (14).
